  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Participatory Community Disaster Risk Reduction - National Coordination</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is developed under the ECHO &apos;Regional Drought Decision III&apos; and hopes to reduce the vulnerability of communities in the north of Kenya  to the recurrent droughts. It has a very systematic approch starting with vulnerability mapping, development and implementation of  disaster plans . It increased awareness on droughts and climate change. A specific result is for capturing of lessons learned, documentation and the cooperation with the regional REGLAP program.    .</narrative>
  </description>
